These two ancient apocryphal orations were included by Vindelinus in his second edition of Sallust's works. The Venice edition's priority is contested, as the real editio princeps for both texts may be an edition printed in Cologne probably in the same year. Differently from the Venice edition the Cologne edition does not include Catilina and Iugurtha.
